payload.message:
That warning comes from Nixpkgs’ recent deprecation of the `system` argument. The fix is to stop passing `system` directly and use the newer `localSystem`/`hostPlatform` shape when importing nixpkgs.

Minimal change in `flake.nix`:

```nix
pkgs = import nixpkgs {
  localSystem = { system = system; };
  overlays = [ zig-overlay.overlays.default ];
};
```

Alternative (also silences it) is to avoid `import` entirely:

```nix
pkgs = nixpkgs.legacyPackages.${system}.extend zig-overlay.overlays.default;
```

If you want, I can apply one of these and confirm the warning is gone with `nix develop --command true`.

